Remaining work is **governance, gating, and alignment**.

---

## A. DECISIONS (FINAL — NO ACTION REQUIRED)

These decisions are fixed and must not be reopened
without explicit justification.

- [x] Fillets are diagnostic artifacts, not knowledge claims
- [x] English is the canonical language
- [x] Fillet types are frozen (no new types)
- [x] Fillets are organized by epistemic level:
  - atomic (E0)
  - claim (E1)
  - structural (E2)
  - meta (E3)
- [x] Structural hierarchy does not imply epistemic hierarchy
- [x] Meta-level artifacts have no privilege
- [x] Legacy artifacts do not gain authority by persistence
- [x] No implicit authority from:
  - history
  - structure
  - consensus
  - success
  - reflexivity

---

## B. REQUIRED GOVERNANCE (OPEN)

These items are **mandatory** before any scale-up,
collaboration, or content production.

### B1. Admissibility Gate

- [ ] Create `Admissibility.md`

Minimum required criteria:
- explicit illegitimate transfer identified
- transfer describable without domain expertise
- at least one counterfactual condition
- clear scope limitation

Explicit exclusions:
- examples without a general pattern
- opinions or normative positions
- rhetorical critiques
- historical commentary without diagnostic value

_No artifact enters the system without passing this gate._

---

### B2. Stop Rules / Exit Criteria

- [ ] Create `Stop_Rules.md`

Must define:
- when analysis stops deliberately
- when justification is considered locally sufficient
- when silence is the correct outcome
- when further decomposition adds no epistemic value

Purpose:
- prevent infinite critique
- prevent meta-authority
- enforce epistemic restraint

---

